[[!meta title="Sound and video"]]

Tails includes several sound and video applications:

  - [*Audacity*](https://www.audacityteam.org/), a multi-track audio editor.

    See the [official documentation](http://manual.audacityteam.org/).

  - [*Brasero*](https://wiki.gnome.org/Apps/Brasero)</span>, an application to
    burn, copy, and erase CDs and DVDs.

    See the [official documentation](https://help.gnome.org/users/brasero/stable/).

  - [*Sound Juicer*](https://wiki.gnome.org/Apps/SoundJuicer)</span>, a CD
    ripper application.

  - [*Sound Recorder*], a sound recorder.

    Sound clips recorded using *Sound Recorder* are saved to the *Recordings*
    folder.

  - [*Videos*], an audio and video player.

These applications can be started from the
